# Code Review Checklist

Reference this checklist when reviewing code changes. Flag violations clearly.

> **Companion rules:**
> - **`code-review-format.mdc`** — defines HOW to present findings (severity tags, layered structure, scope header, build evidence, summary). Every checklist item below maps to a row in the cross-cutting cursor-rules audit table required by that rule.
> - **`verification-before-completion.mdc`** — defines the evidence standard for any "passes / works / done" claim made in a review.
>
> A review is complete only when this checklist is satisfied AND it is presented in the format prescribed by `code-review-format.mdc`.

## Dependency Injection
- [ ] No `@Autowired` — constructor injection via `@RequiredArgsConstructor` only
- [ ] All injected dependencies are `private final`
- [ ] No `new` instantiation of Spring-managed beans

## Security
- [ ] JWT decoding in try-catch — never bubble as 500
- [ ] Public paths in `SecurityConstant.PUBLIC_PATHS`
- [ ] `SessionCreationPolicy.STATELESS`
- [ ] Role checks use `@PreAuthorize` — no custom annotations
- [ ] `AccessDeniedException` → 403, not 500
- [ ] No sensitive headers logged

## Spring Framework
- [ ] No reinvented Spring features — use built-in annotations first
- [ ] No double bean registration (`@Component` + `FilterRegistrationBean`)
- [ ] Security filter chain runs BEFORE interceptors

## Logging
- [ ] `log.debug` for per-request tracing, `log.info` for lifecycle events
- [ ] `log.warn` for 4xx, `log.error` with stack trace for 5xx
- [ ] No logging in tight loops
- [ ] Request/response body logging truncated (max 1KB)

## Configuration
- [ ] Environment values in `application.properties` — not hardcoded
- [ ] Shared constants in `constants/` — not duplicated

## Error Handling
- [ ] All external input has failure handling
- [ ] Custom exceptions mapped in `GlobalExceptionHandler`
- [ ] `GlobalExceptionHandler` extends `ResponseEntityExceptionHandler` — ensures consistent error format for all Spring MVC exceptions
- [ ] Error responses use `ErrorCode` enum
- [ ] Stack traces never exposed to consumers
- [ ] Both `(String)` and `(String, Throwable)` constructors on custom exceptions
- [ ] No `timestamp` in response bodies

## Inter-Service Communication
- [ ] All clients extend `BaseServiceClient`
- [ ] Client named by service, not entity
- [ ] DTOs grouped by service (`dtos/eis/`, `dtos/roster/`)
- [ ] Base URLs include protocol prefix
- [ ] Paginated endpoints use `fetchAllPages()`
- [ ] `ParameterizedTypeReference` for generic responses
- [ ] Downstream errors not exposed raw
- [ ] `ExternalServiceException` → 502, not 500

## Controllers
- [ ] Thin — no business logic
- [ ] `ResponseEntity<ApiResponse<T>>` for success
- [ ] `@Valid` on all `@RequestBody`
- [ ] `@Valid` on nested DTO fields to cascade validation
- [ ] `@PreAuthorize` on all protected endpoints — class level if all endpoints share the same role set
- [ ] Every validation annotation (`@NotNull`, `@NotBlank`, `@Size`, etc.) has a `message` attribute
- [ ] No direct repository/client calls

## Services
- [ ] `@Transactional(readOnly = true)` on reads
- [ ] `@Transactional` on writes
- [ ] No `@Transactional` on `private` methods
- [ ] Correct exception types per failure scenario
- [ ] No HTTP concerns (`HttpStatus`, `ResponseEntity`)

## Repositories
- [ ] Derived methods preferred over `@Query` for simple lookups
- [ ] JPQL + Projection Interface for aggregations (GROUP BY, COUNT) — never `Object[]`
- [ ] Specifications for dynamic filters (search/filter endpoints with optional conditions)
- [ ] Native SQL only for PostgreSQL-specific features
- [ ] `@Param` for named parameters
- [ ] `Optional<T>` for single-entity lookups
- [ ] `default` `getBy...` methods for "get or throw" lookups — avoid repeating `.orElseThrow()` in services
- [ ] No business logic

## Enums
- [ ] No redundant `value` field when string == name
- [ ] `getEnum()` uses `name().equalsIgnoreCase()`

## Entity Auditing
- [ ] Domain entities extend `BaseEntity`
- [ ] No manual `@PrePersist`/`@PreUpdate` for timestamps
- [ ] No `ZoneOffset.UTC` in entities
- [ ] Lookup entities do NOT extend `BaseEntity`

## Lombok on Entities
- [ ] No `@Data` on JPA entities
- [ ] `@AllArgsConstructor` only with concrete need
- [ ] `@ToString.Exclude` on lazy associations
- [ ] Domain: `@Getter @Setter @NoArgsConstructor @EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true, callSuper = false)`
- [ ] Lookup: `@Getter @NoArgsConstructor @EqualsAndHashCode(onlyExplicitlyIncluded = true)`
- [ ] `@EqualsAndHashCode.Include` on `@Id` field
- [ ] `callSuper = false` on domain entities

## Lookup Entities
- [ ] `@Immutable` on all lookup entities
- [ ] `@Cacheable` + `@Cache(READ_ONLY)` present
- [ ] Corresponding `<cache>` region in `ehcache.xml`
- [ ] No `@Setter`, `@Builder`, `@Data`
- [ ] `<Name>Entity` suffix naming

## Column Definitions
- [ ] No `@Column(length = ...)` — Flyway defines sizes
- [ ] `@Column` carries: `name`, `nullable`, `columnDefinition` only

## Redis Caching
- [ ] `@Cacheable` only in `CacheableDataService` — not on repositories or business services
- [ ] `@CacheEvict` only in `CacheEvictionService`
- [ ] Cached values are primitives/DTOs — no JPA entities in Redis
- [ ] Every new cache has a documented eviction trigger in `CacheEvictionService`
- [ ] Every write to cached data calls the corresponding eviction method
- [ ] `sync=true` on high-concurrency caches
- [ ] Explicit `key` attribute — no default `SimpleKey`
- [ ] New cache TTL added in `application.properties` (`cache.ttl.{name}`)
- [ ] `CacheErrorHandler` present — graceful fallback on Redis failure
- [ ] Cache metrics enabled via actuator

## Testing
- [ ] Test plan reviewed before implementation — all scenarios (happy, edge, error) listed upfront
- [ ] Follows Arrange-Act-Assert (AAA) structure
- [ ] Naming: camelCase — `conditionExpectedResult` (inside `@Nested` class that provides method context)
- [ ] `@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)` — NOT `MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this)`
- [ ] `@Nested` for grouping related tests by operation
- [ ] `@ParameterizedTest` for utility/algorithm methods with multiple inputs
- [ ] One logical assertion per test — one behavior per test method
- [ ] No production logic duplicated in tests — hard-code expected values
- [ ] No `Thread.sleep()`, no real external services, no `@Disabled` tests

## Socket-Service Modules
- [ ] New WebSocket modules implement `WebSocketModuleHandler` — not hardcoded in `WebSocketEventProcessor`
- [ ] Each module has its own Redis key prefix — no cross-module key sharing
- [ ] Each module has its own event type enum — not reusing roster's `WebSocketEventType`
- [ ] `ownsConnection()` checks module's own Redis connection key
- [ ] Module-specific logic stays in the handler — processor only routes

## Time & Timezone
- [ ] No `ZonedDateTime.now()`, `LocalDate.now()`, `Instant.now()` without `Clock`
- [ ] All business time operations use injected `Clock` bean — `ZonedDateTime.now(clock)`
- [ ] `Clock` is a `private final` field injected via constructor
- [ ] DB audit timestamps (`@CreationTimestamp`, `@UpdateTimestamp`) remain UTC — not affected by `Clock`

## Query & Data Fetching Optimization
- [ ] Filtering, sorting, and LIMIT happen in the DB — not `stream().filter().limit()` on full result sets
- [ ] No redundant queries — if you already have entity X loaded, don't query the same table again for X's fields
- [ ] Sequential queries merged where possible — prefer JOINs over "fetch IDs → fetch by IDs" patterns
- [ ] External service calls scoped to relevant data — don't fetch all entities when you only need the active subset
- [ ] In-memory grouping uses `Collectors.groupingBy` (O(n)) — not nested `stream().filter()` loops (O(n²))
- [ ] Existence checks use `existsBy...` — not `findBy...` + null check
- [ ] Batch saves via `saveAll()` — not single `save()` in a loop
- [ ] Lazy associations accessed in queries use `JOIN FETCH` — no N+1 loops
- [ ] Queries select only needed columns when full entity is not required
- [ ] Dead/unused repository methods are removed — no orphaned queries

## General
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] Public methods have Javadoc (WHY, not WHAT)
- [ ] No `@Index` — Flyway manages indexes
- [ ] DTOs use classes, not records
- [ ] No business logic in entities
- [ ] No cargo-cult patterns
